# auto-secure

## Context Profile

Load core workspace policy, changed scope, security constraints, and relevant manifests. Never load or retain raw secrets.

## Contract

1. Resolve changed files and sensitive domains; unknown scope fails open to the full audit.
2. Delegate a security audit when the runtime supports it and run stack-appropriate deterministic scanners.
3. Cover access control, cryptography, injection, insecure design, misconfiguration, dependency risk, and secret exposure as applicable.
4. Report exploitable findings first with evidence, severity, affected paths, and remediation. Keep security mandatory in every quality mode.
5. Do not expose credentials, raw provider payloads, or privileged local paths.
